From 64d304c23eaf497291c8c3344298b2682d7c0eb6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Pppery <mapreader@olum.org>
Date: Tue, 23 Dec 2025 18:10:10 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 07/50] Allow to translate command synopses and help

Summary:
Ref T16388

Most of these scripts don't have a way of setting a locale, but if they ever end up with one we may as well wrap things in pht(...). See the test plan for more details.

Doing it to all of them anyway, in the spirit of https://we.phorge.it/book/contrib/article/internationalization/ - we use `pht()` where possible.

Test Plan:
The `src/parser/argument/workflow/PhutilHelpArgumentWorkflow.php` change can be tested by running `arc help --locale en_A*`

I don't think there's any way of setting a locale for the `support/` changes since those scripts don't currently load the locale from arcconfig (and a locale given via `--locale` would render too late), but if there ever becomes such a way then this should work. I think that if T16374 happens then the `--locale` arg would work here.

Reviewers: O1 Blessed Committers, valerio.bozzolan

Reviewed By: O1 Blessed Committers, valerio.bozzolan

Subscribers: tobiaswiese, valerio.bozzolan, Matthew, Cigaryno

Maniphest Tasks: T16388

Differential Revision: https://we.phorge.it/D26608
